The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                A 26-year-old unidentified man died on Wednesday after a trailer hit him on Remount Road. Police said the victim was the driver of another trailer and was standing beside his vehicle. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he was declared dead. Police seized both vehicles but the accused driver fled.     A Dum Dum-bound Metro train developed a snag and came to a halt at Netaji Bhavan station at 10.30am. The services between Tollygunge and Rabindra Sadan were disrupted for almost 30 minutes.    A 21-year-old man was arrested on Tuesday night for selling pirated CDs and DVDs. Police raided a shop in Gariahat and caught Bimal Maity and seized pirated CDs and DVDs worth more than Rs 75,000. A case was registered on the basis of a complaint lodged by the Indian Music Industries.    A fire broke out in a paper godown on Maniktala Main Road at 6.50am on Wednesday. Seven tenders fought the flames for 45 minutes. A fire officer said a short-circuit might have caused the fire. One fireman suffered minor injuries.                                                                                                                                                                
